    "permit_type": "Land Use ReviewType 2 procedureAD: Adjustment",
    "work_description": "Approval of two Adjustments to Zoning Code requirements for the existing apartment building at 2405 NW Irving Street: ¿To increase the amount of vehicle area allowed on the lot from 30% of the lot area to 39.5% (Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.C.4.a.1). ¿To increase the maximum amount of asphalt vehicle area on the lot from 15% of the lot area to 39.5% (Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.C.4.a.2). The approval is per the approved site plan, Exhibit C-1, and subject to the following condition: A.Before the pending Lot Confirmation (PR 25-000913 LC) can be approved, the applicant must obtain final inspection approval of a Zoning Permit that brings the existing perimeter landscaping areas on the north, east, and south sides of the existing parking lot into conformance with the L2 landscaping standard. The landscaping plan must meet all applicable requirements in Zoning Code Chapter 33.248, including but not limited to the L2 landscaping requirements in Zoning Code Section 33.248.020.B.2.",
